Process called "close_file_handle" that takes handle as Any returns Boolean:
    Note: Close file handle using essential runtime calls
    Try:
        Return system_call_file_close with handle as handle
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "quote_json_string" that takes string as String returns String:
    Note: Quote and escape string for JSON
    Let result be quote_character
    Let i be 0
    Let string_length be length of string
    
    While i is less than string_length:
        Let char be character_at_index with string as string and index as i
        Match char:
            When quote_character:
                Set result to result plus "\\" plus quote_character
            When "\\":
                Set result to result plus "\\\\"
            When "/":
                Set result to result plus "\\/"
            When backspace_character:
                Set result to result plus "\\b"
            When form_feed_character:
                Set result to result plus "\\f"
            When newline_character:
                Set result to result plus "\\n"
            When carriage_return_character:
                Set result to result plus "\\r"
            When tab_character:
                Set result to result plus "\\t"
            Otherwise:
                Set result to result plus char
        Set i to i plus 1
    
    Set result to result plus quote_character
    Return result

Process called "serialize_json_array" that takes array as List[JSONValue] returns String:
    Note: Serialize JSON array to string
    Let result be "["
    Let i be 0
    Let array_length be length of array
    
    While i is less than array_length:
        If i is greater than 0:
            Set result to result plus ","
        Set result to result plus serialize with value as (array at index i)
        Set i to i plus 1
    
    Set result to result plus "]"
    Return result

Process called "serialize_json_object" that takes object as Dictionary[String, JSONValue] returns String:
    Note: Serialize JSON object to string
    Let result be "{"
    Let keys_list be keys of object
    Let i be 0
    Let keys_length be length of keys_list
    
    While i is less than keys_length:
        If i is greater than 0:
            Set result to result plus ","
        Let key be keys_list at index i
        Let value be object at key key
        Set result to result plus quote_json_string with string as key plus ":" plus serialize with value as value
        Set i to i plus 1
    
    Set result to result plus "}"
    Return result

Note: JSON type definitions for completeness
Type JSONValue is:
    | JSONNull
    | JSONBoolean with bool_value as Boolean
    | JSONNumber with number_value as Float
    | JSONString with string_value as String
    | JSONArray with array_value as List[JSONValue]
    | JSONObject with object_value as Dictionary[String, JSONValue]

Note: Character constants for JSON escaping
Let quote_character be "\""
Let backspace_character be "\b"
Let form_feed_character be "\f"
Let newline_character be "\n"
Let carriage_return_character be "\r"
Let tab_character be "\t"